nodes.text: Vnex was a location. In the weeks after the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Squadron Four of the Galactic Empire's 204th Imperial Fighter Wing undertook a mission to Vnex, during which no Imperial forces were lost. Upon returning to the planet Pandem Nai, where the 204th had fortified itself following the Battle of Endor, Squadron Four provided Colonel Shakara Nuress with a report that summarized its mission.
Vnex was mentioned in Alphabet Squadron, a novel written by Alexander Freed and published in 2019.
